---
const logItems = [
  "who took the action",
  "what changed",
  "when it changed",
  "why it changed",
  "which workflow item it affected",
  "whether approval was required"
];
---
<section class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 mb-24 reveal">
  <div class="rounded-3xl p-8 md:p-12 border border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800 bg-main dark:bg-stone-950">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-primary dark:text-stone-50 mb-4">
      What we log
    </h2>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted dark:text-stone-400 mb-6">
      For key workflow actions, audit logs should make it clear:
    </p>
    <ul class="grid sm:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-8">
      {logItems.map(item => (
        <li class="flex items-start gap-3 text-sm text-stone-600 dark:text-stone-300">
          <div class="w-1.5 h-1.5 rounded-full bg-amber-600 mt-1.5 flex-shrink-0"></div>
          <span>{item}</span>
        </li>
      ))}
    </ul>
    <p class="text-sm text-muted dark:text-stone-400 leading-relaxed pt-6 border-t border-stone-200 dark:border-stone-800">
      This is especially important for AR workflows involving disputes, PTPs, short-pays, deductions, payment matching, receipt allocation, and manager overrides.
    </p>
  </div>
</section>
